In a call between President Obama and Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko, they discussed the conflict in eastern Ukraine and the upcoming discussions about Ukraine at the G-7 Summit. They expressed concern about the recent assault by Russian-separatist forces near Donetsk and called on Russia and the separatists to adhere to the terms of the Minsk Implementation Plan. President Obama reiterated the United States' support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity, and their commitment to working with international partners to provide assistance for Ukraine's reforms. They also emphasized the need for a diplomatic resolution to the conflict and maintaining costs on Russia and the separatists until they fulfill all provisions of the Minsk agreements.